method.description:
Writes an image to the vision sensor (and applies any image processing via the
vision callback functions
). The vision sensor should be flagged as external input

param.description:
type of the object (sim.sceneobject_shape, sim.sceneobject_joint, etc. (see the 
 object types 
)

name of a color. If a non-empty name is provided, a specific color component is retrieved (e.g. if a shape is a compound shape. If colorName is 

    @compound

, then rgb data for every component of a compound shape is returned)

name of a color. Can be an empty string, but if a name is provided, only shapes (or sub-entities of them) with a same color name will be modified. If colorName is 

    @compound

, then all individual colors of a compound shape can be set at once

filters, e.g.:


filters = {[objectHandle] = {'pose', 'jointPosition', 'layer'}, [sim.handle_scene] = {'engineProperties'}}


filters = {[object1Handle] = {}, [object2Handle] = {'pose'}}


filters = {[sim.handle_sceneobject] = {'pose'}}
